Description:
As Arla, I want to be able to find or to tell which CPH a certain holding has/or even more, what CPH a certain resource type record belongs to.

*   Update HoldingIdentifier/Recipient Reference to unitID_CPH if CPH is present in PII Holding Creator

The CPH will be in the cph field in the `extra` object in the PII export from FM, if applicable.

For example:
~~~
        {
            &quot;farm&quot;: {
                &quot;id&quot;: 491,
                &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Birds Hill Farm&quot;,
                &quot;address&quot;: &quot;Messrs Harrington, Birds Hill Farm, Raughton, Dalston, Cumbria, CA5 7AQ&quot;,
                &quot;postcode&quot;: &quot;CA5 7AQ&quot;
            },
            &quot;unit&quot;: {
                &quot;id&quot;: 491,
                &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Birds Hill Farm&quot;,
                &quot;address&quot;: &quot;M\/s JG &amp; ME Harrington &amp; Son, Birds Hill Farm, Raughton, Dalston, Cumbria, CA5 7AQ&quot;,
                &quot;postcode&quot;: &quot;CA5 7AQ&quot;
            },
            &quot;farmer&quot;: {
                &quot;first_name&quot;: &quot;Richard&quot;,
                &quot;last_name&quot;: &quot;Harrington&quot;
            },
            &quot;extra&quot;: {
                &quot;milk_buyer_number&quot;: &quot;101148000&quot;,
                &quot;cph&quot;: &quot;080680083&quot;
            }
        },
~~~

**Background:**
As a farmer I want my CPH added as&nbsp;part of recipient's reference so that it is available to Arla.

This will need to come in from the PII file (not currently there).&nbsp;

As a CPH is a farm identifier, and a farm may have 2 milk collection points and herds (and hence 2 FM Unit IDs), the CPH will not be unique within Arla, so can't be used as a reference by itself.

I want deletions for Farmmetrics weight records migrated to use the new deletion lambda. 
Use the new deletion lambda setup as was done for treatment programs.&nbsp;(post standardisation)

This may resolve the issue in #30467.

*   Deletion consideration period: 60 days
*   Data Range covered: No restrictions
*   This resource type's data is batched in preprocessing. We will need to make sure to search through all of yesterday's standardised files to detect deletions. (similar behaviour to treatment programs)

**For testing:**
- Weight can be from&nbsp;
  - beef (&quot;integrated-beef&quot;):
    - any of the following pairs:
       - &quot;Birth Weight&quot; AND &quot;Birth Weight Date&quot;
       - &quot;Start of Rearing Weight&quot; AND &quot;Start of Rearing Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;Weaning Weight&quot; AND &quot;Weaning Weight Date&quot;
       - &quot;Start of Growing Weight&quot; AND &quot;Start of Growing Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;Start of Finishing Weight&quot; AND &quot;Start of Finishing Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;Pre Slaughter Weight&quot; AND &quot;Pre Slaughter Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;Start of 1st Grazing Weight&quot; AND &quot;Start of 1st Grazing Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;End of 1st Grazing Weight&quot; AND &quot;End of 1st Grazing Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;Start of 2nd Grazing Weight&quot; AND &quot;Start of 2nd Grazing Weighing Date&quot;
       - &quot;End of 2nd Grazing Weight&quot; AND &quot;End of 2nd Grazing Weighing Date&quot;
    - or values in:
      - &quot;Additional Weights&quot;
      - &quot;Estimated Weights For Age&quot;

From Andrew Cooke:
&gt; This email is to capture the P1 Incident that occurred yesterday, 19 Nov 2025 NZDT four our ISMS Incident Register.
&gt;
&gt;The incident appeared to have been associated with the rollout to production of Keycloak changes that implemented SSO for AMBOSS and Keycloak Admin. It may not have been those changes directly.&nbsp;
&gt;
&gt;The problem appeared to affect Ecosystem APIs and the sharing of authorisation between Appraise and Provider. The Silver Arrows team (Appraise support) were unaware of the changes.
&gt;
&gt;Impacts:
&gt; *   Users could not create accounts in Appraise to start an appraisal
&gt; *   When going to connect data, users had to log into Provider separately although also authenticated with Appraise.
&gt; *   Potentially affected customers and farmers in Saputo Australia, NAB, Rabobank Australia, and affected a demonstration to Rabobank NZ.
&gt;
&gt; Miranda, Neranjan, Chris H, and Daniel - perhaps you could capture some info about the response undertaken.
&gt;
&gt; Chris L and Andrew (and anyone else from the PF team) perhaps you could capture the root cause analysis.
&gt;
&gt; Thanks,
&gt; Andrew.

As part of the data deletion to tidy up after the multiple holdings per unit id incident we need to soft delete (but not update Sainsbury's) animals for the holdings that are copies.&nbsp;

The list of holdings can be found [here](https://dev.azure.com/rezaresystems/15020b92-fee6-4202-956f-9036d1e1da84/_apis/wit/attachments/e8d0d9c7-a34f-4192-b0f6-e8f880440aa4?fileName=holdings_to_dispose.json&amp;download=true). (Please note, this list has not been verified by another person. It would be great if we could verify it before running the deletion. The list of holdings was derived from [fm_unit_ids_across_multple_holdings.json](https://dev.azure.com/rezaresystems/15020b92-fee6-4202-956f-9036d1e1da84/_apis/wit/attachments/863f1468-6d51-4321-a458-26d606de1633?fileName=fm_unit_ids_across_multple_holdings.json&amp;download=true), by simply using earliest connection for a given unit.)

You should expect to see 774,694 deletions.

##Background:
For the duplicated holdings, we have to hard delete the animal data.&nbsp;
This is because Sainsbury's is identifying an animal by ear tag and unit id.&nbsp;
If we soft delete, Sainsburry's will detect this as an animal to be removed but we dont want to remove the animal, just the duplicates.

see [incident teams channel](https://teams.microsoft.com/l/channel/19%3ASNUysZ1Cjc_Ughx36KCaRdx8pimlp81WISOVrSUbGkw1%40thread.tacv2/P2%20Sainsbury%20Incident%20-%20Duplicate%20Data?groupId=85347e60-458a-4d82-b648-4c391f3b1cec&amp;tenantId=0b153499-0343-41cf-9366-e188b68493fd) for details.
